{{zh-forms|alt=𠙿,𠁿,𠮚,𤮺,𠙸,𭺪,𭺫,㤌,金-Cantonese "bitter"}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}} – something sweet in an open mouth; the original drawing is [[𠁿]]. Original form of {{zh-l|*含}}. See also [[敢]], [[旨]], [[香]], and [[音]].

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*klum||sweet}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}} under PTB *klum; STEDT under PTB *s-klum). Cognate with {{cog|lus|thlum}}, {{cog|lep|ᰣᰦᰁᰤᰦᰮ}}.

Possibly related to {{och-l|含|to keep in mouth}} and {{och-l|甜|sweet}}, {{ltc-l|柑|mandarin orange}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

